dcterms:creator: W. H. Kersting
dcterms:description: The IEEE 123 bus test case is used to carry out the task of fault location in distribution systems. It consists of 128 buses, 85 of which are connected to loads, and is utilized to validate the effectiveness of the proposed GCN model.
dcterms:title: IEEE 123 Bus Benchmark System

dcterms:creator: R. C. Dugan
T. E. McDermott
dcterms:description: OpenDSS software is used to simulate faults in the IEEE 123 bus system, generating training and test datasets for evaluating the fault location models.
dcterms:title: OpenDSS Software

dcterms:creator: W. H. Kersting
dcterms:description: The IEEE 37 bus system is implemented to verify the performance of the GCN model in a different distribution network context.
dcterms:title: IEEE 37 Bus System
